<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ken1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ken,</orth> subst. discerning by the eye, sight, eyeshot: <cit><quote>to drown in k. of shore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1114" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1114</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>within a k. our army lies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>losing k. of Albion's wished coast,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 113</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou wast within a k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 6</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>